FBIS3-37611 "drsov035_d_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Feb 1994 Regional Affairs Yeltsin Appoints Omsk Representative MK1902130094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 19 Feb 94 p 2 MK1902130094 Moscow SEGODNYA Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Unattributed report under the "Provincial Chronicle" rubric: "Omsk"] [Text] President Yeltsin has appointed Boris Vasilyevich Tyulkov his representative in Omsk Oblast. Meanwhile, Valeriy Roshchupkin, chairman of the Coordinating Council for Industrial Policy of the "Siberian Agreement" association, has said that $7 million has been transferred from Moscow to the Omsk-based Baranov Engine Making Association's hard-currency account toward payments for military aircraft engines sold to Iran over a year ago under a $35 million contract. Moscow has just begun to settle accounts with the enterprise, although the customer paid the money long ago.
